Vaccination is financed and conducted solely within the public sector. Vaccination is planned in three stages:
• Stage 1: covering the workforce in the health and social sectors, both public and private; this stage started on 27 December 2020;
• Stage 2: covering the population at high risk (older people, patients with chronic diseases, people with disabilities, the homeless) and the essential services workforce (police, defence, transport, economy, administration, etc); this stage started on 15 January 2021;
• Stage 3: general population.

Romania, 21 March:
The Ministry of Internal Affairs recommends that "[...] between 6.00h - 22.00h, the movement of persons outside the home/household is [...] to
be done only for the following reasons:
a) for professional purposes, including from home/household to the location/locations where the professional activity takes place and back;
b) for purchasing goods that cover the basic needs of persons and pets/domestic animals, as well as goods needed for professional activity;
c) for medical assistance which cannot be postponed or performed remotely;
d) for justified reasons, such as to ensure child care/attendance, attendance or assistance to elderly, sick or disabled persons, or the death of a family member;
e) short exits nearby home/household, for individual physical activity of persons and for the needs of pets/domestic animals."
The policy has no explicit end date.

The County Committee for Emergency Situations decided, by Decision no. 11 of January 19, 2021, the extension, until February 2, inclusive, of the measures corresponding to the incidence rate of more than 3/1,000 inhabitants, valid at the time of the adoption of this decision.
- Movement outside the home/household is prohibited between 11:00 p.m. and 5:00 a.m., with certain exceptions;
- Wearing a protective mask is mandatory for all people who have reached the age of 5 in closed or open public spaces, in public transport or at work;

Mayor George Scripcaru will propose to the City Council, in tomorrow's meeting, the purchase and distribution of protective masks for approximately 6,000 vulnerable people in the municipality of Brașov, after obtaining, during today's day, the approval of the Local Committee for Emergency Situations. This proposal comes in the context in which the Ministry of Health could not yet implement the provisions of GEO no. 78 of May 21, 2020* through which he had to provide protective masks for families and disadvantaged people.
The following categories of people will benefit from these free masks:

a) persons from beneficiary families of the social aid granted on the basis of Law no. 416/2001 regarding the guaranteed minimum income, with subsequent amendments and additions – 172 persons;
b) persons from families receiving allowance for family support granted on the basis of Law no. 277/2010 regarding the allowance for family support, republished, with subsequent amendments and additions - 173 persons;
c) pensioners of the public pension system who have reached the age of 65 and whose rights are up to 704 lei inclusive, representing the level of the social allowance for pensioners provided by the Government Emergency Ordinance no. 6/2009 regarding the establishment of the guaranteed minimum social pension, approved by Law no. 196/2009, with subsequent amendments – 3,897 people;
d) disabled persons who earn income exclusively from the social benefits provided by art. 42 and 58 of Law

The employees of the Social Assistance Directorate distribute the masks to disadvantaged people at home.
The entitled persons are:
- persons from beneficiary families of the social aid granted on the basis of Law no. 416/2001 regarding the guaranteed minimum income, with subsequent amendments and additions;
- persons from families receiving allowance for family support granted on the basis of Law no. 277/2010 regarding the family support allowance, republished, with subsequent amendments and additions;
beneficiaries of the public pension system, with pensions up to 800 lei inclusive (for example survivor's pension, disability pension or social pension);
- disabled persons who earn income exclusively from social benefits.
A number of 50 protective masks are granted for each person, related to a period of 2 months, based on supporting documents (identity card, pension coupon, disability certificate).

Entitled persons are expected to pick up their protective masks directly, at the headquarters of the Brașov Social Assistance Directorate, in Pamsofor str., no. 2. 3.

