Romania, March 23, 2020:
The Romanian National Institute of Public Health / National Center for Surveillance and Control of Communicable Diseases (CNSCBT) recommends to prioritize the testing of the following groups of persons for SARS-CoV-2 (in descending order):
1. Symptomatic persons with a history of international travel;
2. Symptomatic close contacts of confirmed cases;
3. Symptomatic medical staff;
4. Cases of SARI [severe acute respiratory infection; W.H.] with no other aetiology, from ALL age groups and from
ALL hospitals;
5. Symptomatic institutionalised persons
Testing is ONLY done on the recommendation of the doctor, both in the public system,
and in private health care.
The ending of this policy is indefinite.

"Green" areas: countries where the cumulative incidence rate of new COVID-19 cases in the last 14 days is less than or equal to 1,5 per 1000 inhabitants;
"Yellow" areas: countries where the cumulative incidence rate of new COVID-19 cases in the last 14 days is between 1,5 and 3 per 1000 inhabitants;
"Red" areas: countries where the cumulative incidence rate of new COVID-19 cases in the last 14 days is greater than or equal to 3 per 1000 inhabitants.

