In order to protect citizens who come into contact with Brașov City Hall officials, but also to protect the institution's employees, Mayor Allen Coliban ordered new measures to prevent the spread of the coronavirus inside Brașov City Hall:
- starting this week, the employees of each service or office will have staggered work schedules inside the compartment;
- where possible, the office schedule will be mixed: part of the employees will be teleworking or in the field, and another part will be in the office;
– where it is not possible to use this system, some of the employees will be moved to other offices that are not used, to reduce the number of employees in a room;
- at the level of the mayor's office, an analysis of the outstanding holidays will be made these days, so that, where possible, the officials will go on holiday;
- in order to eliminate contact between officials from different departments, communication between officials between different offices and services will be done only electronically and by telephone;
- special spaces will be created for the signing of documents, outside the offices, which will be periodically disinfected;
- in order to eliminate contact between officials and people outside the town hall, the access of people other than civil servants, local councilors and employees of public institutions in relation to the Town Hall, in the town hall building, is strictly prohibited. Citizens will have access to the Information Center for Citizen

